<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
        <link rel="stylesheet"
        href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0-beta/css/bootstrap.min.css"
        integrity="sha384-/Y6pD6FV/Vv2HJnA6t+vslU6fwYXjCFtcEpHbNJ0lyAFsXTsjBbfaDjzALeQsN6M"
        crossorigin="anonymous">
        <title>Gasconade</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <h1>Gasconade</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                Getting annoyed by "threads" in <a href="https://twitter.com/">Twitter?</a> Wish they'd written a blog post?<br />
                Want that blog post right now? Give me the tweet url!</p>
            <form action="/tweet" method="POST">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="twitter_url">Tweet URL</label>
                    <input type="url"
                        name="twitter_url"
                        class="form-control"
                        required pattern="https://twitter.com/[^/]+/status/(\d+)"
                        oninvalid="this.setCustomValidity('Please enter a Twitter \'tweet\' URL here')"
                        oninput="setCustomValidity('')"
                        placeholder="https://twitter.com/foo/status/12345" />
                </div>
                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Get blog post</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>